\newlabel{fig_1}{{1}{5}{Representative fibril segments generated with the DLA algorithm containing 30,000 molecules. Panels $(a)$ and $(b)$ show typical fibrils obtained with $T_s = 2$ (short-term diffusion) and $T_s = 8192$ (long-term diffusion), respectively. Colors indicate the relative time of attachment, from early (blue) to late (red)}{figure.1}{}}
