\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {8}{\ignorespaces The average fraction of molecules removed in a cluster, $\Psi $, as a function of normalized force $F_n = F/F_{\mathrm  {rup}}$ for $T_s = 8, 32, 128$ and $8192$. For low $T_s$, local failure due to molecules detaching in clusters contributes significantly even at low forces, indicating early onset of collective failure. In contrast, for high $T_s$, damage accumulation in the fibril initially is driven by isolated bond breakings, whereas rupture in cluster (and catastrophic failure) occurs only near full fibril rupture.}}{13}{figure.8}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig_8}{{8}{13}{The average fraction of molecules removed in a cluster, $\Psi $, as a function of normalized force $F_n = F/F_{\mathrm {rup}}$ for $T_s = 8, 32, 128$ and $8192$. For low $T_s$, local failure due to molecules detaching in clusters contributes significantly even at low forces, indicating early onset of collective failure. In contrast, for high $T_s$, damage accumulation in the fibril initially is driven by isolated bond breakings, whereas rupture in cluster (and catastrophic failure) occurs only near full fibril rupture}{figure.8}{}}
